						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the third <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This inscription in Sanskrit engraved in late characters, mentions Ānandēśvara and Dēvatīrtha. Records a certain pious act done by <hi rend="italic">Brāhmaṇas.</hi></p>						

